    "headline": "First shutout of the year and it felt like a proper release valve.",
    "vibe": "32-0 over the Tigers, five tries, Rinakama unstoppable down the edge and Hayward tackling like a man possessed on 39. The kind of complete performance we've been begging for. Doesn't fix the season — we're still 10th and staring down a Warriors side flying — but it's the first time in weeks the Kennel wasn't at each other's throats.",
    "kennelMood": "Quietly relieved",
    "kennelSummary": "Post-Tigers vibe was 'don't get carried away but that was nice'. Curran's double got a lot of love, Rinakama's 297m had people asking why we ever leave him out, and there was a brief ceasefire in the Ciraldo wars. Preston contract drama immediately took over the airtime anyway.",
